<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-358-582  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 358 582.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Digital Review  June 12 1989 v6 n23 p57(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Ziff-Davis Publishing Co. 1989.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Ardent's big backer invests another $50M.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Gianatasio, David.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Ardent Computer Corp. (finance)Kubota Ltd. (investment activities).andO;Topic:     InvestmentsSupercomputersGovernment ContractsDiagnostic EquipmentArtificial IntelligenceScientific ResearchSpace Flight.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>Ardent's Big Backer Invest Another $50MandM;Personal supercomputer maker Ardent Computer of Sunnyvale, Calif., hasreceived $50 million from Kubota of Osaka, Japan, the company's principalinvestor, more than doubling the level of Kubota's previous investment.andP;  Themoney will be used to fund a variety of projects, including the completion ofa &quot;broad family of computers,&quot; scheduled for a fall release, Ardent officalssaid.andP;  These computers will include a low-cost desktop supercomputer as wellas minisupercomputer offerings, the officials said.andM;BUSINESSWATCHandM;The Institute of High Energy Physics of the Virginia Polytechnic Instituteand State University at Blacksburg, Va., has installed a supercomputermanufactured by Convex Computer of Richardson, Texas.andP;  According to physicsprofessor Luke W. Mo, the Convex C210 system will run very large, complexapplications programs used to analyze the underlying principles of physics inthe study of the structure of matter.andM;Vance Systems of Chantilly, Va., has been awarded a $350,000 Small BusinessInnovative Research Phase 2 contract by the U.S.andP;  Navy.andP;  Under the deal,Vance will develop automated local area network diagnostic tools usingartificial intelligence and expert-system technology.andP;  For the past threeyears, Vance has been working with the Navy to define conformance-testprocedures for the Shipboard Advanced Fiber-Optic Embedded Network (Safenet)program.andP;  The Safenet program is recommending the use of IEEE 802 and ANSIX3T9.5 LAN protocol standards for connecting computers aboard ships.andM;DEC presented former NASA administrator James C. Fletcher with the &quot;DigitalDiscovery Award&quot; fir continued excellence in science.andP;  The award waspresented by DEC President Kenneth Olsen at Washington's Air and SpaceMuseum.andP;  While at NASA, Fletcher oversaw the Apollo 17 moon landing as wellas the Apollo-Soyuz space linkup.andO;</TEXT></DOC>